-- Italy's Petacchi Wins His 2nd Tour de France Stage; Cancellara Keeps Lead
-- Alex Duff
-- 2010-07-07T15:41:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/italy-s-petacchi-wins-his-2nd-tour-de-france-stage-cancellara-keeps-lead.html

          
          
             Italyâ€™s Alessandro Petacchi won stage
four of the Tour de France as Fabian Cancellara of Switzerland
kept the race-leading yellow jersey.  
 Petacchi, who rides for the Lampre team, won in a sprint
finish for his second stage win of this edition. Defending
champion Alberto Contador and seven-time winner Lance Armstrong
were among race contenders to finish in the main pack after the
flat 95-mile ride between Cambrai and Reims.  
          
          


  


        